TextBody:
Hi Chandan,

It is unfortunate that you have encountered this issue.

1) Did you already successfully reset the password for the "svcStealthAudit" account and confirm that you can remote desktop into the server indicated in the screenshot attached to this case before running the NEA job? 

2) From what I can see in the screenshot, you are attempting to remote desktop (RDC) into the computer on the "FICOCLOUDDEV.COM" domain and the message indicates that "the user account is disabled and cannot be used".  I believe that you need to contact your internal IT support and/or network/domain administrator and ask them to enable the "svcStealthAudit" account on that domain.  Until this issue is resolved, NEA will continue to error with the message that "The supplied credential is invalid".

Thank you,
Mike Candon
Senior Technical Support Engineer
